ost and faith regained.The first comprehensive history of American Judaism in over fifty years, this book is both a celebration of 350 years of Jewish life in America and essential reading for anyone interested in American religion and life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aJewsxHistoryxUnited States. 0aJewszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aJudaismxHistoryxUnited States. 0aJudaismzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aJudaïsmexHistoirexÉtats-Unis. 0aJuifsxHistoirexÉtats-UnisxUnited States. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300129106423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300129106.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles